{
  "texts": [
    "Several transitions performed in the sit and stand postures are determined as the physiologically important function.",
    "Quantitative validations in monitoring the human's daily activity need a reliable and objective mechanism to be utilized in daily living conditions 19.",
    "Validating the energy expenditure is accepted as the standard physical activity computation measure.",
    "However, these procedures are impractical for general conditions and are also not feasible for the clinical environment 20.",
    "The indirect and direct energy expenditure metrics employ various measurement-based approaches by considering the heart rate recordings, questionnaires, motion captures, and observations 21."
  ]
}